<h2>Description</h2>
<p>The clearWatch method cancels an ongoing watchPosition call. When cancel=
led, the watchPosition call stops retrieving updates about the current geog=
raphic location of the device.</p>
<h2>Syntax</h2>
<p>Here is the syntax of this method =E2=88=92</p>
<pre class=3D"result notranslate">clearWatch(watchId);
</pre>
<h2>Parameters</h2>
<p>Here is the detail of parameters =E2=88=92</p>
<ul class=3D"list">
<li><p><b>watchId</b> =E2=88=92 This specifies the unique ID of the watchPo=
sition call to cancel. The ID is returned by the watchPosition call.</p></l=
i>
</ul>
<h2>Return value</h2>
<p>The clearWatch method does not return a value.</p>
